## ZSH
- Installation
$ brew install zsh

- Set ZSH as default shell
$ sudo -s 'echo /usr/local/bin/zsh >> /etc/shells' && chsh -s /usr/local/bin/zsh

## Oh My ZSH
- Installation
$ sh -c "$(curl -fsSL https://raw.github.com/robbyrussell/oh-my-zsh/master/tools/install.sh)"

## Oh My ZSH Theme >> bullet-train
- Download
https://github.com/caiogondim/bullet-train-oh-my-zsh-theme

- Put the file bullet-tain.zsh-theme to $ZSH_CUSTOM/themes/ via this script
$ sudo mkdir $ZSH_CUSTOM/themes
$ cp ~/Download/bullet-train-oh-my-zsh-theme $ZSH_CUSTOM/themes/

- Config .zshrc file to use bullet-train theme
ZSH_THEME = "bullet-train"

## Powerline
- Download and install Powerline to support theme UI
$ git clone git@github.com:jeremyFreeAgent/oh-my-zsh-powerline-theme.git
$ cd oh-my-zsh-powerline-theme/
$ ./install_in_omz.sh

- Download and install Powerline Font
$ git clone git@github.com:powerline/fonts.git
$ cd fonts/
$ ./install.sh


## VIM Plugins
- Install vim pathogen
$ cd ~/.vim/bundle && git clone https://github.com/tpope/vim-sensible.git

- NerdTree
$ git clone https://github.com/scrooloose/nerdtree.git ~/.vim/bundle/nerdtree

- Ctrl-P >> for searching file name and easy open.
$ cd ~/.vim && git clone https://github.com/kien/ctrlp.vim.git bundle/ctrlp.vim
